<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sound-n">sound <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /saʊnd/    美 /saʊnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>声；声音：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Light travels faster than sound.
光比声音传播得快。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He slided into the house trying not to <strong>make a sound</strong>.
他偷偷地溜进房里，尽量不发出一点儿声音。</p></div>

<h3 id="noise-sound-voice">辨析 noise, sound, voice</h3>
<p><strong>noise ** 通常指不悦耳的、令人烦恼的嘈杂声，隐含贬义。
</strong>sound ** 是普通用词，含义笼统，指人们能听到的各种声音，无褒贬色彩。
**voice ** 指人说话或唱歌时发出的声音。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’ll have to <strong>raise your voice</strong> if you want to be heard in here. 
在这里，如果想让别人听见你说话，你必须大点儿声。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could hear angry voices in the next room. 
我能听到隔壁房间的怒吼声。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(广播、电视等的) 音响；音量：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is a sound engineer.
他是位音响师。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Turn the sound down / up a little, will you?
把音量调低/高一点儿好吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>[常用复数] 音乐：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I need to buy some new sounds.
我要买些新的音乐了。</p></div></div>